omq.client.annotation

Annotation Type RemoteInterface


  • @Documented
@Retention(value=RUNTIME)
@Target(value=TYPE)
public @interface RemoteInterface
    Annotation which indicates which is the remote interface that can have asynchmethods or syncmethods. By default every method without an annotation will be classified as a SyncMethod. Both annotations can be preceded by the @MultiMethod annotation.
    Author:
    Sergi Toda
